                          <p>The faculty offers four year undergraduate courses in Computer Science and Engineering and has plans to start graduate courses in the near future. The courses cover subjects like computer programming, data structure, algorithms, compiler construction, computer network and architecture telecommunication engineering, analog and digital electronics, image processing and multimedia etc. The courses have been designed so that students graduating from this department have a balance of theory and practical skills to prepare them for the highly competitive workplace. In spite of resource constraints, care is taken so that high teaching quality is maintained at each stage of education.</p>
